dekaf2 provides CMake targets:

    find_package(dekaf2 CONFIG REQUIRED)
    target_link_libraries(main PRIVATE dekaf2::dekaf2)

    # SQL convenience libraries (link the one matching an enabled backend):
    target_link_libraries(main PRIVATE dekaf2::ksql2)     # mysql / postgres / freetds
    target_link_libraries(main PRIVATE dekaf2::ksqlite)   # sqlite

dekaf2 is a framework - most capabilities are optional features.

  Enabled by default: sqlite, yaml, useragent, http2, http3, compression, zip
  Opt-in database backends (pick the one(s) you need):
      mysql      MySQL / MariaDB
      postgres   PostgreSQL
      freetds    MS SQL Server (FreeTDS)

Select features in classic mode:

    vcpkg install dekaf2[core,mysql,postgres]
    vcpkg install dekaf2[*]            # build everything dekaf2 offers

or in manifest mode (vcpkg.json):

    "dependencies": [
        { "name": "dekaf2", "features": [ "mysql", "postgres" ] }
    ]

List every feature with its description any time:

    vcpkg search dekaf2
